  "title": "Full Time Admin Assistant (Operation Dept)",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for Part-Time Admin Assistant (Operation Department) for daily operation to manage client / a pool of floater and cleaner queries, schedule and feedbacks …. etc . Must be details, good at follow up and hgood time management. Need to manage and monitor equipment, cleaning solutions and cleaning standard.<br /></p><p><strong>Work Day:</strong></p><p>5 Weekdays + 1 Weekend<br /></p><p><strong>Work Shift:</strong></p><p>7am to 4pm or 2pm to 11pm<br /></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Able to communicate well/fast with client, floater and cleaner through various channels (e.g phone calls, Chat / SMS, emails, walk-ins)</li><li>Maintaining a positive, empathetic, and professional attitude toward clients at all times Responding promptly to client inquiries & complaints Ensure client satisfaction and provide professional client support</li><li>To arrange floater or cleaner jobs schedule and monitor cleaning standard. Collect mails and documents</li><li>Assist in any ad hoc duties assigned by Executive or Assistant Executive</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 1 year experience in customer service, scheduling</li><li>Minimum 'O' holder Customer-oriented with good interpersonal and communication skills</li><li>Pleasant and friendly personality Strong problem solving capabilities</li><li>Able to work at a fast pace environment, fast learner, willing to take up responsibility Computer literacy</li></ul>",
